Clinical and pathological features of the hormonal clusters are presented in Fig. 3A. Accordingly, cluster #2 and #3 patients exhibited, respectively, the best and poorest progression-free survival (p = 0.042). Analogical yet not significant effects were observed for relapse-free survival (ns (p = 0.056)). Hormonal cluster #1 patients were exposed to intermediate-to-high risk of progression and relapse. Progression and relapse risk in cluster #4 was low-to-intermediate (Fig. 3B, Supplementary Figure S5).Fig. 3
